ror instead of descriptive message","-- `.codeharness/workflows/default.yaml` hardcoded in 7+ locations","-","-**Coverage:** 96.64% overall, all files above 80% floor.","-","-## Token Report","-- Total tool calls: 18","-- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 8, Edit: 3, Grep: 0, Write: 0, Glob: 1, Skill: 1","-- Largest Bash outputs: `npx vitest run --coverage` (~60 lines), `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` (~10 lines)","-- Files read: 9 unique, 10 total reads","-- Redundant operations: None","-","-### 2-4-init-command-workflow-generation — verification (2026-04-02T14:55)","-","-- **Proof format issue:** First proof document didn't match parser's expected `## AC N:` top-level format with `bash`/`output` code block pairs. Returned 0/8 verified. Rewrote proof in correct format.","-- **AC 4 weak evidence:** `--force` in help verified via source code grep of Commander.js `.option()` registration rather than `--help` invocation. Sufficient for test-provable tier.","-- **BATS test failures:** onboard, ralph, verify_gates, validate_epic_docs all fail with code 127 — legacy scripts deleted in story 1-2. Pre-existing, doesn't affect vitest suite.","-- **48 lint warnings:** All pre-existing unused-var/regex issues in other modules.","-","-## Token Report","-- Total tool calls: 16","-- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 2, Grep: 5, Write: 1","-- Largest Bash outputs: `npm test` (~80 lines), `npx vitest run --coverage` (~40 lines)","-- Files read: 2 unique, 2 total reads","-- Redundant operations: Ran npm test twice, coverage command twice — could have been combined","-","-### 2-5-validate-command — create-story (2026-04-02T14:50)","-","-**Problems encountered:**","-- Existing `validate.ts` command (story 10-3, self-validation/release gate) conflicts with v2 architecture's `validate.ts` (schema validation). Epics file's AC is brief and doesn't acknowledge this.","-","-**Workarounds applied:**","-- AC #6 explicitly addresses the naming collision, asks dev to make structural decision at implementation time.","-","-**Risks identified:**","-- Command restructuring (AC #6) could break existing self-validation consumers, though no known programmatic callers.","-","-**Observations:**","-- Story 2-5 is last in Epic 2. Ties together schema (2-1), parser (2-2), embedded template (2-3), init command (2-4).","-- Epics-v2 AC unusually terse — story expanded to 8 specific, testable ACs.","-","-## Token Report","-- Total tool calls: 18","-- By tool: Bash: 3, Read: 10, Glob: 5, Write: 1, Skill: 1","-- Largest Bash outputs: `git diff --stat` (~5 lines), `grep validate` (~8 lines), `git log --oneline` (~5 lines)","-- Files read: 10 unique, 10 total reads","-- Redundant operations: None","-","-### 2-5-validate-command — dev-story (2026-04-02T14:55)","-","-- **Boundary test enforcement:** Project requires all `catch` blocks to have `// IGNORE:` comment, rethrow, or `Result.fail()`. Initial `catch {}` tripped this — fixed.","-- **Pre-existing TS errors:** `tsc --noEmit` produces many errors (project uses custom build pipeline). Known issue.","-- **No `src/index.ts` changes needed:** Export name/signature stayed the same.","-","-## Token Report","-- Total tool calls: 18","-- By tool: Bash: 5, Read: 8, Edit: 4, Grep: 2, Write: 4, Glob: 2, Skill: 1","-- Largest Bash outputs: `tsc --noEmit` (~80 lines), `vitest run` full suite (~30 lines)","-- Files read: 9 unique, 9 total reads","-- Redundant operations: None","-","-### 2-5-validate-command — code-review (2026-04-02T15:02)","-","-**Bugs found:**","-- HIGH: DRY violation — copy-paste of rendering logic between validate.ts and validate-schema.ts (FIXED)","-- MEDIUM: Missing test for non-WorkflowParseError exception path (FIXED)","-","-**Code quality issues NOT fixed (LOW):**","-- `process.chdir()` in tests mutates global state; could use vi.spyOn instead","-- No `--dir` option for programmatic use from different working directories","-","-**Coverage:** 96.65% overall. validate-schema.ts: 100%. validate-self.ts: 98.07% (pre-existing gaps).","-","-## Token Report","-- Total tool calls: 21","-- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 12, Edit: 6, Glob: 1, Skill: 1","-- Largest Bash outputs: `npm test` (~170 lines), `codeharness coverage` (~5 lines)","-- Files read: 11 unique, 13 total reads","-- Redundant operations: 1 re-read of validate-schema.test.ts (justified offset read)","-","-### 2-5-validate-command — verification (2026-04-02T15:08)","-","-- **AGENTS.md stale:** `codeharness verify` precondition failed — missing entries for validate-schema.ts and validate-self.ts. Documentation housekeeping, not an AC failure.","-- **Coverage branch gap:** validate-schema.ts 75% branch coverage (uncovered lines 36, 38). Edge-case branches in imported module.","-- **AC evidence quality:** ACs #1 and #2 rely on unit test assertions rather than live CLI invocation. Appropriate for test-provable tier.","-","-## Token Report","-- Total tool calls: 14","-- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 1, Grep: 2, Write: 1","-- Largest Bash outputs: `vitest --coverage` (~60 lines), `npm run test:unit` (~50 lines)","-- Files read: 1 unique, 1 total reads","-- Redundant operations: Ran vitest coverage twice (once combined, once isolated)"]}],"originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-02\n\n### 2-3-default-embedded-workflow — create-story (2026-04-02T11:46)\n\n- **No problems encountered.** All artifacts located and readable.\n- **Workaround:** Skipped sprint-status.yaml update as instructed (orchestrator owns status writes).\n- **No risks identified.** All 8 ACs are `test-provable`.\n- **Observation:** `templates/workflows/` directory does not exist yet — this story creates it.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Bash: 2, Read: 11, Glob: 5, Grep: 2, Write: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `ls templates/` (~15 lines), `git log --oneline -5` (~5 lines)\n- Files read: 13 unique, 14 total reads\n- Redundant operations: None\n\n### 2-3-default-embedded-workflow — code-review (2026-04-02T14:14)\n\n**Bugs found:** None (implementation was correct)\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority):**\n- Tests are integration tests depending on real filesystem and parseWorkflow(). No unit-level mocks. Acceptable for static YAML story.\n- Default workflow YAML has no comments explaining design rationale.\n\n**Coverage gaps:** None. All 150 files above 80% floor. Overall 96.63%.\n\n**Architecture concerns:** None.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:** None.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 21\n- By tool: Bash: 11, Read: 6, Edit: 1, Grep: 0, Write: 1, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npx vitest run --coverage | tail -50` (~50 lines), `npx codeharness coverage --min-file 80` (~5 lines), `npx vitest run | tail -10` (~10 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 8 total reads\n- Redundant operations: 5 grep attempts on coverage output returning empty due to ANSI color codes\n\n### 2-3-default-embedded-workflow — verification (2026-04-02T14:25)\n\n- **BATS test warnings**: Multiple BATS integration tests emit BW01 warnings about deleted scripts (ralph.sh, onboard.sh, verify_gates.sh, validate_epic_docs.sh). Pre-existing from story 1-2.\n- **Proof format requirement**: Initial proof failed codeharness verify (0/8 ACs) because validator requires `bash` blocks followed by `output` blocks as evidence. Rewrote in expected format.\n- **Coverage reporting granularity**: Coverage output truncates long filenames, making confirmation harder. Cross-referenced with path.\n- **No exec-plan**: Warning about missing exec-plan — not part of verification request but flagged in story verification requirements.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Bash: 12, Read: 4, Write: 1, Grep: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npm test` tail (~80 lines), `npx vitest run --coverage` tail (~40 lines)\n- Files read: 3 unique, 4 total reads\n- Redundant operations: Ran npm test twice, multiple coverage commands with different grep patterns due to filename truncation\n\n### 2-4-init-command-workflow-generation — create-story (2026-04-02T14:25)\n\n**Problems encountered:**\n- The workflow references `workflow.md` but actual file is `workflow.yaml`. Wrong extension in skill trigger.\n- `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` path referenced in workflow.yaml does not exist — it is at `_bmad/config.yaml`.\n- No `project-context.md` exists in this project.\n- Story key doesn't appear verbatim in epics file (uses \"Story 2.4\" not kebab-case).\n\n**Workarounds applied:**\n- Skipped sprint-status.yaml update per orchestrator instruction.\n- Skipped web research step — no external libraries involved.\n- Skipped validation checklist invocation — intended for interactive review.\n\n**Risks identified:**\n- None. All ACs are test-provable (file copy + CLI flag addition).\n\n**Observations:**\n- Init command is well-structured at 68 lines. Adding workflow generation is ~20 lines into `initProjectInner()`.\n- `handleRerun()` path returns early and skips generation steps. Workflow generation with `existsSync` check handles re-runs naturally.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 24\n- By tool: Bash: 5, Read: 10, Glob: 8, Grep: 7, Write: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `ls _bmad/bmm/workflows/` (~5 lines), `git log --oneline -5` (~5 lines)\n- Files read: 12 unique, 12 total reads\n- Redundant operations: 3 Glob attempts before finding workflow directory structure\n\n### 2-4-init-command-workflow-generation — dev-story (2026-04-02T14:35)\n\nNo issues reported. Implementation clean — 30/30 tests pass, build succeeds.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Bash: 4, Read: 8, Edit: 10, Grep: 0, Write: 0, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit` (~30 lines), `npx vitest run init-project.test.ts` (~8 lines), `npm run build` (~10 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 9 total reads\n- Redundant operations: None\n\n### 2-4-init-command-workflow-generation — code-review (2026-04-02T14:45)\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- MEDIUM: `handleRerun()` ignored `--force` flag for workfl