{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019oGoa4Tg3mdyT4T4B9uSag","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 2.5: Validate Command\n2\t\n3\tStatus: verifying\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a developer,\n10\tI want `codeharness validate` to check my workflow and agent YAML files against their JSON schemas,\n11\tso that I catch configuration errors before running.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** a project with `.codeharness/workflows/default.yaml` that is valid\n16\t   **When** `codeharness validate` runs\n17\t   **Then** the command exits 0 and reports each validated file with `[OK]` status\n18\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n19\t\n20\t2. **Given** a project with a malformed workflow YAML (e.g., missing required `tasks` key)\n21\t   **When** `codeharness validate` runs\n22\t   **Then** the command exits 1 and reports the file path, schema violation path, and specific error message for each violation\n23\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n24\t\n25\t3. **Given** a workflow YAML with a dangling task reference in `flow` (references a task not defined in `tasks`)\n26\t   **When** `codeharness validate` runs\n27\t   **Then** the command exits 1 and the error message identifies the dangling reference by name and its location in the flow array\n28\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n29\t\n30\t4. **Given** no `.codeharness/workflows/` directory exists in the project\n31\t   **When** `codeharness validate` runs\n32\t   **Then** the command exits 1 and reports `[FAIL] No workflow files found` (not a crash or unhandled exception)\n33\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n34\t\n35\t5. **Given** `codeharness validate --json` runs against a project with one valid and one invalid YAML\n36\t   **When** the output is parsed as JSON\n37\t   **Then** it contains `{ status: 'fail', files: [...] }` where each file entry has `{ path, valid, errors }` and `errors` is an array of `{ path, message }` objects\n38\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n39\t\n40\t6. **Given** the existing `codeharness validate` command (self-validation, story 10-3)\n41\t   **When** `codeharness validate` runs after this change\n42\t   **Then** the schema validation behavior is exposed as a subcommand (`codeharness validate schema`) OR the existing validate command is replaced, with the old self-validation functionality moved to `codeharness validate self` — choose whichever preserves backward compat better. The chosen approach must be documented in dev notes.\n43\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n44\t\n45\t7. **Given** the `parseWorkflow()` function from `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts`\n46\t   **When** `codeharness validate` validates a workflow file\n47\t   **Then** it reuses `parseWorkflow()` for schema + referential integrity checking (does NOT duplicate validation logic)\n48\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n49\t\n50\t8. **Given** unit tests for the validate command\n51\t   **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n52\t   **Then** tests pass covering: valid workflow reports OK, invalid workflow reports errors with file path and violation details, missing directory reports no-files-found, JSON output shape is correct, exit codes are correct (0 on success, 1 on failure), and no regressions in existing validate tests\n53\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n54\t\n55\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n56\t\n57\t- [x] Task 1: Decide command structure — subcommands vs replacement (AC: #6)\n58\t  - [x] Evaluate whether to add `validate schema` subcommand or restructure `validate` with `validate self` / `validate schema`\n59\t  - [x] The existing `validate` command (self-validation) has no known external consumers calling it programmatically, so either approach works. Document decision in dev notes.\n60\t\n61\t- [x] Task 2: Implement the schema validation command handler (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4, #5, #7)\n62\t  - [x] Create a new command registration function (e.g., `registerValidateSchemaCommand`) or modify existing `registerValidateCommand`\n63\t  - [x] Discover `.codeharness/workflows/*.yaml` files in the project directory\n64\t  - [x] For each discovered YAML file, call `parseWorkflow(filePath)` and catch `WorkflowParseError`\n65\t  - [x] Map `WorkflowParseError.errors` to user-facing output with file path, violation path, and message\n66\t  - [x] Handle missing directory gracefully (no crash)\n67\t  - [x] Set `process.exitCode = 0` if all files valid, `process.exitCode = 1` if any invalid\n68\t\n69\t- [x] Task 3: Implement JSON output mode (AC: #5)\n70\t  - [x] When `--json` is set, output `{ status: 'pass' | 'fail', files: [{ path, valid, errors }] }`\n71\t  - [x] Use `jsonOutput()` from `src/lib/output.ts`\n72\t\n73\t- [x] Task 4: Restructure existing validate command if needed (AC: #6)\n74\t  - [x] If subcommand approach chosen: register as `validate schema` and rename existing to `validate self`\n75\t  - [x] If replacement approach: move self-validation to `validate self`, make `validate` default to schema validation\n76\t  - [x] Update `src/index.ts` command registration\n77\t\n78\t- [x] Task 5: Write unit tests (AC: #8)\n79\t  - [x] Test: valid workflow YAML exits 0 with OK output\n80\t  - [x] Test: invalid workflow YAML exits 1 with error details including file path and violation\n81\t  - [x] Test: dangling task reference is caught and reported\n82\t  - [x] Test: missing `.codeharness/workflows/` directory exits 1 with informative message\n83\t  - [x] Test: JSON output has correct shape\n84\t  - [x] Test: no regressions in existing validate (self-validation) tests\n85\t\n86\t## Dev Notes\n87\t\n88\t### Module Location and Architecture Role\n89\t\n90\tThe architecture (AD1) states CLI commands are thin wrappers calling modules. The validate command should:\n91\t- Live at `src/commands/validate.ts` (already exists for self-validation — must restructure)\n92\t- Delegate all schema validation logic to `parseWorkflow()` from `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts`\n93\t- NOT duplicate any validation logic — the workflow parser already does schema validation + referential integrity\n94\t\n95\t### Command Structure Decision\n96\t\n97\tThe existing `validate.ts` implements self-validation (story 10-3, release gate checking). Story 2-5 needs schema validation. Two options:\n98\t\n99\t**Option A (recommended): Subcommands**\n100\t```\n101\tcodeharness validate schema   # NEW: validate YAML files against schemas\n102\tcodeharness validate self     # EXISTING: self-validation release gate\n103\tcodeharness validate          # Default: run schema validation (most common use)\n104\t```\n105\t\n106\t**Option B: Replace and move**\n107\tMove self-validation to a separate command entirely.\n108\t\n109\tThe dev should choose based on what preserves backward compat best. Commander.js supports subcommands via `program.command('validate').command('schema')`.\n110\t\n111\t### Reusing parseWorkflow()\n112\t\n113\tThe `parseWorkflow()` function in `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` already:\n114\t1. Reads the YAML file from disk\n115\t2. Parses YAML syntax\n116\t3. Validates against `workflow.schema.json` via Ajv\n117\t4. Checks referential integrity (dangling task references in `flow`)\n118\t5. Throws `WorkflowParseError` with structured `.errors` array\n119\t\n120\tThe validate command should simply:\n121\t1. Discover files in `.codeharness/workflows/*.yaml`\n122\t2. Call `parseWorkflow()` for each file\n123\t3. Catch `WorkflowParseError` and format the `.errors` for user output\n124\t4. Report results\n125\t\n126\tDo NOT create a separate validation module or re-implement schema checking.\n127\t\n128\t### File Discovery Pattern\n129\t\n130\tUse `globSync` or `readdirSync` to find `*.yaml` and `*.yml` files under `.codeharness/workflows/`. The architecture specifies workflows live here (AD3). Agent YAML validation (in `templates/agents/`) will be added in Epic 3 stories — for now, only workflow files need validation.\n131\t\n132\t### Output Conventions\n133\t\n134\tFollow the established patterns from `src/lib/output.ts`:\n135\t- `ok('Schema: .codeharness/workflows/default.yaml valid')` — green `[OK]`\n136\t- `fail('Schema: .codeharness/workflows/custom.yaml invalid')` — red `[FAIL]`\n137\t- Error details indented below the fail line\n138\t\n139\t### Exit Code Convention\n140\t\n141\t- Exit 0: All discovered files are valid\n142\t- Exit 1: Any file is invalid OR no files found OR command error\n143\t- This matches the existing convention in `validate.ts` and other commands\n144\t\n145\t### JSON Output Shape\n146\t\n147\t```typescript\n148\tinterface ValidateSchemaResult {\n149\t  status: 'pass' | 'fail';\n150\t  files: Array<{\n151\t    path: string;\n152\t    valid: boolean;\n153\t    errors: Array<{ path: string; message: string }>;\n154\t  }>;\n155\t}\n156\t```\n157\t\n158\t### What This Story Does NOT Do\n159\t\n160\t- Does NOT validate agent YAML files (no `agent.schema.json` exists yet — that's story 3.1)\n161\t- Does NOT implement workflow patching or resolution (story 9.1)\n162\t- Does NOT change `parseWorkflow()` or `schema-validate.ts` — those are already complete from stories 2.1 and 2.2\n163\t- Does NOT add new schemas — only uses the existing `workflow.schema.json`\n164\t\n165\t### Anti-Patterns to Avoid\n166\t\n167\t- **Do NOT re-implement schema validation** — `parseWorkflow()` already does it all\n168\t- **Do NOT read YAML and call Ajv directly** — go through `parseWorkflow()` for the full check (schema + referential integrity)\n169\t- **Do NOT put business logic in the command file** — keep it thin, but note that file discovery + loop is simple enough to stay in the command\n170\t- **Do NOT break existing `validate` self-validation tests** — restructure carefully\n171\t- **Do NOT validate files outside `.codeharness/workflows/`** — that's the defined location\n172\t\n173\t### Existing Test Patterns\n174\t\n175\tThe existing `validate.ts` tests (if any) test self-validation. For schema validation tests, follow the pattern in `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-parser.test.ts`:\n176\t- Mock `fs.readFileSync` or use temp files\n177\t- Test both valid and invalid YAML inputs\n178\t- Assert on specific error messages and paths\n179\t\n180\t### Dependencies from Previous Stories\n181\t\n182\t- **Story 2.1** created `src/schemas/workflow.schema.json` — the schema to validate against\n183\t- **Story 2.2** created `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` with `parseWorkflow()` and `WorkflowParseError` — the validation engine\n184\t- **Story 2.3** created `templates/workflows/default.yaml` — a known-valid workflow for positive testing\n185\t- **Story 2.4** created the init command that copies the default workflow to `.codeharness/workflows/` — so `validate` has files to discover\n186\t\n187\t### Git Intelligence\n188\t\n189\tRecent commits follow the pattern `feat: story X-Y-slug — description`. Files are organized with commands in `src/commands/`, modules in `src/lib/` or `src/modules/`, tests co-located in `__tests__/` directories. All stories in this epic build on the workflow-parser module.\n190\t\n191\t### Project Structure Notes\n192\t\n193\t- Modified file: `src/commands/validate.ts` — restructure to support schema validation alongside existing self-validation\n194\t- Modified file: `src/index.ts` — update command registration if structure changes\n195\t- New test file: `src/commands/__tests__/validate-schema.test.ts` (or extend existing validate test file)\n196\t- No changes to `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` or `src/lib/schema-validate.ts` — they're already complete\n197\t\n198\t### References\n199\t\n200\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-v2.md#Story 2.5: Validate Command]\n201\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD1: Module Decomposition — validate.ts as thin wrapper]\n202\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD3: Embedded Template Storage — .codeharness/workflows/ location]\n203\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-parser.ts — parseWorkflow(), WorkflowParseError, validation pipeline]\n204\t- [Source: src/lib/schema-validate.ts — validateWorkflowSchema(), Ajv integration]\n205\t- [Source: src/commands/validate.ts — existing self-validation command to restructure]\n206\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/2-4-init-command-workflow-generation.md — init copies default.yaml to .codeharness/workflows/]\n207\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/2-2-workflow-parser-module.md — parseWorkflow API, error structure]\n208\t\n209\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n210\t## Verification Requirements\n211\t\n212\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/2-5-validate-command-proof.md)\n213\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n214\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n215\t\n216\t## Documentation Requirements\n217\t\n218\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n219\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/2-5-validate-command.md\n220\t\n221\t## Testing Requirements\n222\t\n223\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n224\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n225\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n226\t\n227\t## Dev Agent Record\n228\t\n229\t### Agent Model Used\n230\t\n231\tClaude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n232\t\n233\t### Debug Log References\n234\t\n235\tN/A\n236\t\n237\t### Completion Notes List\n238\t\n239\t- **Command structure decision (Task 1):** Chose Option A — subcommands. `validate` defaults to schema validation (most common use), `validate schema` is explicit, `validate self` preserves existing self-validation. This preserves backward compat since `validate self` still works and the default behavior changes to the more commonly needed schema validation.\n240\t- Self-validation logic extracted to `validate-self.ts`, schema validation in `validate-schema.ts`, parent command in `validate.ts`.\n241\t- `runSchemaValidation()` is exported as a pure function for testability, separate from CLI concerns.\n242\t- `src/index.ts` required no changes — `registerValidateCommand` function name and signature unchanged.\n243\t- Existing validate self-validation tests updated to use `validate self` subcommand path.\n244\t- All 3632 tests pass (147 test files), zero regressions.\n245\t\n246\t### File List\n247\t\n248\t- `src/commands/validate.ts` — restructured as parent command with subcommands; uses shared `renderSchemaResult()` (modified)\n249\t- `src/commands/validate-schema.ts` — schema validation command handler + `runSchemaValidation()` + `renderSchemaResult()` (modified in review: extracted shared render helper, eliminated DRY violation)\n250\t- `src/commands/validate-self.ts` — extracted self-validation logic from old validate.ts\n251\t- `src/commands/__tests__/validate.test.ts` — updated for `validate self` subcommand (modified)\n252\t- `src/commands/__tests__/validate-schema.test.ts` — test file with 16 tests covering all ACs + non-WorkflowParseError edge case (modified in review)\n253\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01FLHeMC7z4edzYfkx1nRfuA","session_id":"fb9c1538-17c2-48c5-8d63-6a9f60fb8dd3","uuid":"047bed53-2e55-418a-8df9-ab1ffe9913b0","timestamp":"2026-04-02T15:11:41.034Z"}
