{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014KGxyv9QuuQnc666zxiS9g","type":"tool_result","content":"8:  - research/domain-harness-design-long-running-agents-research-2026-04-01.md\n9:  - research/technical-ai-agent-verification-testing-research-2026-03-16.md\n26:**Functional Requirements:** 43 FRs across 10 capability areas — Workflow Definition (6), Agent Configuration (6), Workflow Configuration (3), Workflow Execution (8), Adversarial Verification (5), Feedback Loop (3), Circuit Breaker (4), Observability (2), CLI Commands (4), Legacy Removal (2).\n28:**Non-Functional Requirements:** 18 NFRs across Performance (5), Reliability (5), Integration (4), Code Quality (4). Architecture-critical NFRs: crash recovery via state persistence (NFR6-8), programmatic agent dispatch only (NFR11), optional observability (NFR14).\n39:- Dependencies: `commander`, `yaml`, `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk`\n40:- Execution substrate: Agent SDK `query()` — async generator, session management, JSON schema output\n47:1. **Config resolution** — every agent/workflow dispatch resolves embedded → user → project patches\n48:2. **Trace ID propagation** — generated per iteration, injected into agent prompts, correlates to observability\n69:| **New** | @anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk | Research — replaces bash spawn |\n80:3. Evaluator verdict schema — the contract between evaluator and engine\n83:4. Embedded template storage — where agent/workflow YAML files live in the package\n95:| `workflow-parser` | Parse YAML, validate against JSON schema, resolve patches (embedded→user→project) | FR1-6, FR13-15 |\n96:| `agent-resolver` | Resolve agent config through patch chain, compile to SDK inline subagent definition | FR7-12 |\n98:| `agent-dispatch` | Call Agent SDK `query()`, manage sessions (fresh/continue), inject trace IDs | FR19-23 |\n103:**Rationale:** 7 modules, each 100-200 LOC. Feedback loop (FR29-30) is part of `workflow-engine` — it's loop logic, not a separate concern. CLI commands (`init`, `run`, `validate`, `status`) are thin wrappers calling these modules. Observability (FR36-37) is a cross-cutting concern handled by trace ID injection in `agent-dispatch`, not a separate module.\n115:Engine copies story files to temp dir, spawns evaluator with `cwd` set to this directory. Agent SDK options enforce isolation:\n120:**Rationale:** Simplest approach. Source isn't there because we never put it there. No git worktree complexity, no Docker-in-Docker. The Agent SDK's `cwd` + `disallowedTools` provide sufficient isolation.\n128:  agents/\n144:**Rationale:** Files over compiled strings. Easier to inspect, diff, and debug. The `codeharness init` command copies the default workflow to the project; embedded agents are resolved at runtime from the package location.\n152:2. Resolve all referenced agents: same resolution chain → cache\n157:### AD5: Evaluator Verdict Schema\n159:**Decision:** Structured JSON enforced by Agent SDK `jsonSchema` option.\n185:**Rationale:** Replaces the 175-line proof document regex parser entirely. The Agent SDK validates the output against this schema — if the evaluator doesn't produce valid JSON, the SDK rejects it. Every AC verdict requires evidence (commands + output), enforcing the anti-leniency principle structurally.\n192:3. `agent-resolver` — resolve agent configs, needed before dispatch\n193:4. `agent-dispatch` — SDK integration, needed before engine can run\n200:- `evaluator` depends on `agent-dispatch` (for SDK spawn) and `workflow-state` (for verdict recording)\n202:- `agent-dispatch` depends on `agent-resolver` (for compiled subagent definitions)\n208:**File naming:** `kebab-case.ts` for all source files. Already established (`workflow-parser.ts`, `agent-dispatch.ts`).\n212:**YAML keys:** `snake_case` for all workflow and agent config keys (`source_access`, `max_budget_usd`).\n224:Embedded templates: `templates/agents/`, `templates/workflows/`.\n225:User-level: `~/.codeharness/agents/`, `~/.codeharness/workflows/`.\n226:Project-level: `.codeharness/agents/`, `.codeharness/workflows/`.\n231:**Evaluator verdict:** JSON schema enforced (AD5). No alternative formats. Every AC requires `status`, `evidence.commands_run`, `evidence.output_observed`.\n243:| Agent timeout | Score as UNKNOWN, continue |\n245:| Missing embedded agent | Fatal error at startup |\n258:**Session boundary enforcement:** `session: fresh` = new Agent SDK query with no resume/continue. No session reuse optimization across tasks.\n262:**All agents implementing codeharness v2 MUST:**\n264:- Use Agent SDK `query()` for all agent dispatch — never `execFileSync`\n266:- Use `bare: true` for all programmatic agent spawns\n292:│   │   ├── validate.ts                    # NEW — schema validation command\n312:│   │   ├── workflow-parser.ts             # YAML parse, schema validate, patch resolution\n313:│   │   ├── agent-resolver.ts             # Agent config resolution, SDK compilation\n315:│   │   ├── agent-dispatch.ts             # Agent SDK query(), sessions, trace IDs\n350:│   └── schemas/                           # JSON schemas (NEW)\n351:│       ├── workflow.schema.json\n352:│       ├── agent.schema.json\n353:│       └── verdict.schema.json\n356:│   ├── agents/                            # 9 agent YAMLs (8 BMAD + evaluator)\n402:- `verify-prompt.ts` — Black-box verifier prompt (replaced by evaluator agent YAML)\n449:- 7 core modules in `src/lib/` (workflow-parser, agent-resolver, workflow-engine, agent-dispatch, evaluator, circuit-breaker, workflow-state)\n\n[Showing results with pagination = limit: 50]"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01FLHeMC7z4edzYfkx1nRfuA","session_id":"fb9c1538-17c2-48c5-8d63-6a9f60fb8dd3","uuid":"dff0e362-a9f3-4765-ae8f-2a2094f3d5bd","timestamp":"2026-04-02T15:12:03.527Z"}
