{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FDQ59oukxHV2LCxbyUUvdP","type":"tool_result","content":"36:[Omitted long matching line]\n40:This overhaul restructures codeharness around **team-role modules** — infra, dev, review, verify, sprint — each owning one responsibility completely. It adds OpenSearch as a remote observability backend and agent-browser for real browser verification. The release gate: codeharness verifies its own 65-story codebase overnight, unattended. When it passes, the product is credible. Until then, it isn't.\n47:- **Project-agnostic.** CLIs, plugins, web apps, libraries, APIs — all get verified. The harness adapts HOW (docker exec, agent-browser, API calls) but never refuses.\n55:- **Complexity:** Medium-High — orchestrates Docker, VictoriaMetrics/OpenSearch, agent-browser, OTel, autonomous loops\n143:7. **Agent-browser verification** — Real browser verification for web projects.\n241:[OK] agent-browser: installed\n248:### Journey 4: The Web App Verification (Agent-Browser Path)\n250:**Sam, next day.** A story requires verifying that a login page works. The verifier uses agent-browser:\n255:docker exec codeharness-verify agent-browser navigate http://localhost:3000/login\n256:docker exec codeharness-verify agent-browser screenshot login-page.png\n257:docker exec codeharness-verify agent-browser click \"[ref=email-input]\"\n258:docker exec codeharness-verify agent-browser type \"test@example.com\"\n259:docker exec codeharness-verify agent-browser click \"[ref=submit-btn]\"\n260:docker exec codeharness-verify agent-browser screenshot after-login.png\n272:| Web App Verify | Agent-browser integration, screenshot capture, accessibility-tree interaction |\n280:2. **Team-role architecture for agent orchestration.** Instead of pipeline orchestration (step→step→step), modules are organized like team members with independent failure domains. The QA module can timeout without killing Sprint Management. This is a structural answer to \"autonomous agents are fragile.\"\n282:3. **Operational learning loop.** Patches update from real failure modes discovered during autonomous operation. Session retros generate action items. Action items feed into patches. Patches change agent behavior. The harness gets better at verification as it discovers what fails — without model changes.\n299:codeharness is a **dual-distribution developer tool**: npm CLI package (`codeharness`) + Claude Code plugin (`.claude-plugin/`). The CLI does all mechanical work (Docker, verification, state management). The plugin provides slash commands, hooks, and agent-facing skills that invoke the CLI.\n323:│   │   ├── browser.ts       # Agent-browser verification\n367:**Agent-Browser Integration:**\n401:| 7 | Agent-browser verification | #8 | Real browser verification for web projects |\n466:- **FR16:** Verifier can use agent-browser to navigate web UIs, interact with elements, and capture annotated screenshots as evidence\n542:- **NFR20:** Patches shall be markdown files readable by both humans and agents, not embedded code strings."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01FLHeMC7z4edzYfkx1nRfuA","session_id":"fb9c1538-17c2-48c5-8d63-6a9f60fb8dd3","uuid":"f856bee4-1f95-4f8d-a583-87fac93a3cd8","timestamp":"2026-04-02T15:12:24.499Z"}
