{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_016752hMEgd4Sepo7yhs1a8D","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01YXdq5yELRpNXeCeW2rcafm","name":"Grep","input":{"pattern":"FR7|FR8|FR9|FR10|FR11|FR12|agent config|persona|traits|PersonaNexus","path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md","output_mode":"content","-n":true,"head_limit":30},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":839,"cache_read_input_tokens":58887,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":839,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":56,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01FLHeMC7z4edzYfkx1nRfuA","session_id":"fb9c1538-17c2-48c5-8d63-6a9f60fb8dd3","uuid":"2a0149a7-32dd-4dd2-92cd-1116b6188077"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YXdq5yELRpNXeCeW2rcafm","type":"tool_result","content":"38:3. **A multi-level agent and workflow configuration system.** Agents and workflows exist at three levels: embedded (ships with codeharness), user-level, and project-level — with hybrid patching to customize without replacing. 9 embedded agents (8 BMAD + evaluator) and 1 default workflow ship out of the box. Agent personality uses BMAD-compatible fields as the base with optional PersonaNexus-compatible traits for fine-grained behavioral tuning.\n47:- **Agent-as-assignee with structured personality.** Tasks are assigned to specific agents with BMAD personas and optional quantified personality traits (warmth, rigor, directness, etc.). The evaluator is tuned for high rigor and zero leniency.\n54:- **Complexity:** High — workflow engine, multi-agent orchestration, session isolation, agent configuration system, observability integration, major legacy rework\n56:- **Design Philosophy:** Declarative-first — YAML workflows and agent configs drive behavior\n107:9. Multi-level agent configuration (embedded/user/project) with hybrid patching\n119:- PersonaNexus-compatible trait compilation (quantified personality → prompt instructions)\n124:- Agent marketplace — community-contributed agent configs\n183:  personality:\n184:    traits:\n198:Alex installs Docker but has no BMAD project set up. `codeharness init` reports: \"No BMAD agent configs found at `_bmad/bmm/agents/`. Run BMAD setup first, or use `--skip-bmad` to use only embedded agents.\"\n234:1. For each `per-story` task in flow order: resolve agent config (embedded → user → project patches) → compile to SDK inline subagent → generate trace ID → spawn session (fresh or continue) → pass input contract → collect output\n265:BMAD-compatible base fields (required) with optional PersonaNexus-compatible traits:\n272:persona:\n278:# Optional: quantified personality\n279:personality:\n280:  traits:\n294:~/.codeharness/agents/      # personal agent customizations\n295:~/.codeharness/workflows/   # personal workflows\n338:- FR7: System ships 9 embedded agents: dev, qa, architect, pm, sm, analyst, ux-designer, tech-writer, evaluator\n339:- FR8: User can create custom agents at project level (`.codeharness/agents/`) or user level (`~/.codeharness/agents/`)\n340:- FR9: User can patch embedded or user-level agents via `extends:` with structured `overrides:` and freeform `prompt_patches:`\n341:- FR10: Agent config supports BMAD-compatible base fields (name, role, persona with identity/communication_style/principles) and optional PersonaNexus-compatible traits (10 dimensions, 0-1 scale)\n342:- FR11: System resolves agent config through embedded → user → project patch chain at runtime\n343:- FR12: System compiles resolved agent config into Claude Code inline subagent definition for SDK dispatch\n422:- NFR7: Evaluator session timeout does not crash the engine — timeout is a scored failure, not a fatal error\n423:- NFR8: All engine state is persisted to disk after each task completion\n424:- NFR9: Engine handles programmatic agent dispatch API errors gracefully (API limits, network failures) with specific error reporting\n425:- NFR10: Long-running executions (4+ hours) do not degrade in correctness or accumulate resource leaks\n429:- NFR11: Engine uses the official programmatic agent dispatch API — no direct CLI process spawning\n430:- NFR12: BMAD agent configs are read-only — engine never modifies agent YAML files"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01FLHeMC7z4edzYfkx1nRfuA","session_id":"fb9c1538-17c2-48c5-8d63-6a9f60fb8dd3","uuid":"664e1caa-be88-488c-9d84-1fc86e19725a","timestamp":"2026-04-02T15:12:42.880Z"}
