{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PLt3dm9yuKzdVF7gqKW6a8","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 3.1: Agent Config JSON Schema\n2\t\n3\tStatus: verifying\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a developer,\n10\tI want a JSON schema defining valid agent configuration,\n11\tso that malformed agent configs are caught before dispatch.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** `src/schemas/agent.schema.json` exists\n16\t   **When** inspected\n17\t   **Then** the schema requires `name` (string), `role` (object with `title` and `purpose` strings), and `persona` (object with `identity` string, `communication_style` string, and `principles` array of strings) as required fields\n18\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n19\t\n20\t2. **Given** an agent YAML file with all required fields (name, role, persona)\n21\t   **When** validated against the agent schema\n22\t   **Then** validation passes with `{ valid: true, errors: [] }`\n23\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n24\t\n25\t3. **Given** an agent YAML file missing a required field (e.g., no `role`)\n26\t   **When** validated against the agent schema\n27\t   **Then** validation fails with errors identifying the missing required property by path\n28\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n29\t\n30\t4. **Given** an agent YAML file with `personality.traits` where a trait value is outside 0-1 range (e.g., `rigor: 1.5`)\n31\t   **When** validated against the agent schema\n32\t   **Then** validation fails with an error identifying the out-of-range trait and its path\n33\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n34\t\n35\t5. **Given** an agent YAML file with `personality.traits` where all values are within 0-1 range\n36\t   **When** validated against the agent schema\n37\t   **Then** validation passes (personality is optional; when present, traits are validated)\n38\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n39\t\n40\t6. **Given** a `validateAgentSchema()` function exported from `src/lib/schema-validate.ts`\n41\t   **When** called with valid agent config data\n42\t   **Then** it returns `ValidationResult` with `{ valid: true, errors: [] }` using the same `validateAgainstSchema()` pattern as `validateWorkflowSchema()`\n43\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n44\t\n45\t7. **Given** the `codeharness validate` command (story 2-5)\n46\t   **When** agent YAML files exist in `.codeharness/agents/` or `templates/agents/`\n47\t   **Then** the validate command can validate agent files against `agent.schema.json` (integration point — actual command wiring is story 3-2 or later; this story only ensures the schema + validation function are available)\n48\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n49\t\n50\t8. **Given** unit tests for agent schema validation\n51\t   **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n52\t   **Then** tests pass covering: valid agent passes, missing required fields fail, traits outside 0-1 rejected, optional `personality` section accepted when present and valid, optional `disallowedTools` array accepted, unknown top-level properties rejected, and no regressions in existing schema-validate tests\n53\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n54\t\n55\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n56\t\n57\t- [x] Task 1: Create the agent JSON schema (AC: #1, #4, #5)\n58\t  - [x] Create `src/schemas/agent.schema.json` following the same JSON Schema draft-07 pattern as `workflow.schema.json`\n59\t  - [x] Define required properties: `name`, `role` (with `title`, `purpose`), `persona` (with `identity`, `communication_style`, `principles`)\n60\t  - [x] Define optional `personality` section with `traits` object where each value is a number constrained to 0-1 via `minimum: 0, maximum: 1`\n61\t  - [x] Define optional `disallowedTools` as an array of strings (needed for evaluator agent)\n62\t  - [x] Set `additionalProperties: false` at top level to reject unknown fields\n63\t\n64\t- [x] Task 2: Add agent schema validation function (AC: #6, #7)\n65\t  - [x] Import agent schema in `src/lib/schema-validate.ts`\n66\t  - [x] Compile the agent schema with Ajv (same pattern as workflow schema)\n67\t  - [x] Export `validateAgentSchema(data: unknown): ValidationResult` that delegates to `validateAgainstSchema()`\n68\t  - [x] Ensure the existing `validateWorkflowSchema()` and `validateAgainstSchema()` remain unchanged\n69\t\n70\t- [x] Task 3: Write unit tests (AC: #2, #3, #4, #5, #8)\n71\t  - [x] Create `src/lib/__tests__/schema-validate-agent.test.ts` (or extend existing `schema-validate.test.ts`)\n72\t  - [x] Test: valid agent config with all required fields passes\n73\t  - [x] Test: valid agent config with optional `personality.traits` in 0-1 range passes\n74\t  - [x] Test: missing `name` field fails\n75\t  - [x] Test: missing `role` field fails\n76\t  - [x] Test: missing `persona` field fails\n77\t  - [x] Test: `personality.traits.rigor: 1.5` fails (above 1)\n78\t  - [x] Test: `personality.traits.warmth: -0.1` fails (below 0)\n79\t  - [x] Test: valid `disallowedTools: [\"Edit\", \"Write\"]` passes\n80\t  - [x] Test: unknown top-level property rejected\n81\t  - [x] Test: existing workflow schema validation still works (no regressions)\n82\t\n83\t## Dev Notes\n84\t\n85\t### Module Location and Architecture Role\n86\t\n87\tPer architecture-v2 AD1, `agent-resolver` resolves agent config through patch chain and compiles to SDK inline subagent definition (FR7-12). This story creates the **schema** that `agent-resolver` (story 3-3) will use for validation. The schema lives at `src/schemas/agent.schema.json` alongside the existing `workflow.schema.json`.\n88\t\n89\tThe validation function lives in `src/lib/schema-validate.ts` — the module already has a generic `validateAgainstSchema()` helper and a workflow-specific `validateWorkflowSchema()`. Add `validateAgentSchema()` following the exact same pattern.\n90\t\n91\t### Agent Config Shape (from PRD and Architecture)\n92\t\n93\tThe canonical agent config format from prd-evaluator-redesign.md:\n94\t\n95\t```yaml\n96\tname: evaluator\n97\trole:\n98\t  title: Adversarial QA Evaluator\n99\t  purpose: Exercise the built artifact and determine if it actually works\n100\tpersona:\n101\t  identity: Senior QA who trusts nothing without evidence\n102\t  communication_style: Blunt, evidence-first\n103\t  principles:\n104\t    - Never give the benefit of the doubt\n105\t    - Every PASS requires evidence\n106\t# Optional: quantified personality\n107\tpersonality:\n108\t  traits:\n109\t    rigor: 0.98\n110\t    directness: 0.95\n111\t    warmth: 0.2\n112\t```\n113\t\n114\t**Required fields:**\n115\t- `name` (string) — agent identifier\n116\t- `role.title` (string) — agent's role title\n117\t- `role.purpose` (string) — what this agent does\n118\t- `persona.identity` (string) — who this agent is\n119\t- `persona.communication_style` (string) — how it communicates\n120\t- `persona.principles` (array of strings) — behavioral principles\n121\t\n122\t**Optional fields:**\n123\t- `personality.traits` — object with string keys and number values constrained to 0-1 range (PersonaNexus-compatible, FR10)\n124\t- `disallowedTools` — array of strings (used by evaluator agent for source isolation, per AD2)\n125\t\n126\t### JSON Schema Pattern to Follow\n127\t\n128\tFollow the existing `workflow.schema.json` pattern exactly:\n129\t- `\"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"`\n130\t- `\"$id\": \"https://codeharness.dev/schemas/agent.schema.json\"`\n131\t- Use `definitions` for reusable sub-schemas if needed\n132\t- `additionalProperties: false` at all object levels\n133\t\n134\t### Trait Validation Detail\n135\t\n136\tPersonaNexus traits are an `additionalProperties` object where each value must be `{ \"type\": \"number\", \"minimum\": 0, \"maximum\": 1 }`. The trait names are not fixed — any string key is allowed as long as the value is 0-1. Use `additionalProperties` with a number schema inside the `traits` object.\n137\t\n138\t### What This Story Does NOT Do\n139\t\n140\t- Does NOT create agent YAML files (that's story 3-2)\n141\t- Does NOT implement the agent resolver module (that's story 3-3)\n142\t- Does NOT wire agent validation into the `validate` command (future integration — this story only provides the schema + validation function)\n143\t- Does NOT implement patch resolution (extends, overrides, prompt_patches) — that's the resolver in story 3-3\n144\t- Does NOT add `templates/agents/` to `package.json` `files` array (that's story 3-2)\n145\t\n146\t### Anti-Patterns to Avoid\n147\t\n148\t- **Do NOT create a separate Ajv instance** — reuse the existing one in `schema-validate.ts`\n149\t- **Do NOT put schema validation logic in a new file** — extend `schema-validate.ts`\n150\t- **Do NOT define trait names as an enum** — PersonaNexus traits are open-ended (any 0-1 number)\n151\t- **Do NOT make `personality` required** — it's optional per FR10 (\"optional PersonaNexus-compatible traits\")\n152\t- **Do NOT modify `workflow.schema.json`** — this story only adds agent schema\n153\t\n154\t### Dependencies from Previous Stories\n155\t\n156\t- **Story 2.1** established the `src/schemas/` directory and `workflow.schema.json` — same directory for `agent.schema.json`\n157\t- **Story 2.1** established the `schema-validate.ts` module with `validateAgainstSchema()` — the generic helper to reuse\n158\t- **Story 2.5** established the `validate` command with subcommand structure — future stories will wire agent validation into it\n159\t\n160\t### Existing Test Patterns\n161\t\n162\tFollow the pattern in existing tests:\n163\t- Tests are co-located in `src/lib/__tests__/`\n164\t- Use vitest (`describe`, `it`, `expect`)\n165\t- Test both valid and invalid inputs\n166\t- Assert on specific error paths and messages from `ValidationResult`\n167\t\n168\t### Git Intelligence\n169\t\n170\tRecent commits follow `feat: story X-Y-slug — description`. The codebase uses TypeScript with ESM (`\"type\": \"module\"`), vitest for testing, and tsup for building. All modules are single files in `src/lib/` with co-located tests in `__tests__/`.\n171\t\n172\t### Project Structure Notes\n173\t\n174\t- New file: `src/schemas/agent.schema.json` — the agent configuration JSON schema\n175\t- Modified file: `src/lib/schema-validate.ts` — add `validateAgentSchema()` export\n176\t- New test file: `src/lib/__tests__/schema-validate-agent.test.ts` (or extend existing test file)\n177\t- No changes to any other existing files\n178\t\n179\t### References\n180\t\n181\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-v2.md#Story 3.1: Agent Config JSON Schema]\n182\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD1: Module Boundaries — agent-resolver module]\n183\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD3: Embedded Template Storage — templates/agents/]\n184\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#Agent Configuration Format — canonical YAML shape]\n185\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#FR7-FR12 — Agent Configuration FRs]\n186\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#NFR2 — Agent config resolution <200ms]\n187\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#NFR12 — BMAD agent configs read-only]\n188\t- [Source: src/schemas/workflow.schema.json — pattern to follow for JSON schema structure]\n189\t- [Source: src/lib/schema-validate.ts — existing validation module to extend]\n190\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/2-5-validate-command.md — validate command structure for future integration]\n191\t\n192\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n193\t## Verification Requirements\n194\t\n195\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/3-1-agent-config-json-schema-proof.md)\n196\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n197\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n198\t\n199\t## Documentation Requirements\n200\t\n201\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n202\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/3-1-agent-config-json-schema.md\n203\t\n204\t## Testing Requirements\n205\t\n206\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n207\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n208\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n209\t\n210\t## Dev Agent Record\n211\t\n212\t### Agent Model Used\n213\t\n214\tClaude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n215\t\n216\t### Debug Log References\n217\t\n218\t### Completion Notes List\n219\t\n220\t- All 3 tasks completed: schema, validation function, tests\n221\t- 29 new agent schema tests pass, 28 existing workflow schema tests unaffected\n222\t- Full test suite: 3662 tests pass across 148 files\n223\t\n224\t### Code Review Notes (Adversarial)\n225\t\n226\t- **Fixed**: Schema accepted empty strings for all fields — added `minLength: 1` to `name`, `role.title`, `role.purpose`, `persona.identity`, `persona.communication_style`, and principles items\n227\t- **Fixed**: Schema accepted empty `principles` array — added `minItems: 1`\n228\t- **Fixed**: Schema accepted `personality: {}` without `traits` key — made `traits` required inside `personality`\n229\t- **Fixed**: Missing tests for empty string rejection, empty collection rejection, `personality` without `traits`, and non-string `disallowedTools` items\n230\t- Post-review: 39 agent schema tests pass (was 29), 28 workflow schema tests unaffected\n231\t- Coverage: 96.65% overall, all 152 files above 80% floor, `schema-validate.ts` at 100%\n232\t\n233\t### File List\n234\t\n235\t- `src/schemas/agent.schema.json` — new agent configuration JSON schema\n236\t- `src/lib/schema-validate.ts` — added `validateAgentSchema()` export\n237\t- `src/lib/__tests__/schema-validate-agent.test.ts` — new test file with 29 tests\n238\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fb9c1538-17c2-48c5-8d63-6a9f60fb8dd3","uuid":"fd2a60ac-9d09-458b-b168-c6d48bf05d8c","timestamp":"2026-04-02T15:21:55.659Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/3-1-agent-config-json-schema.md","content":"# Story 3.1: Agent Config JSON Schema\n\nStatus: verifying\n\n<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n\n## Story\n\nAs a developer,\nI want a JSON schema defining valid agent configuration,\nso that malformed agent configs are caught before dispatch.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. **Given** `src/schemas/agent.schema.json` exists\n   **When** inspected\n   **Then** the schema requires `name` (string), `role` (object with `title` and `purpose` strings), and `persona` (object with `identity` string, `communication_style` string, and `principles` array of strings) as required fields\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n2. **Given** an agent YAML file with all required fields (name, role, persona)\n   **When** validated against the agent schema\n   **Then** validation passes with `{ valid: true, errors: [] }`\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n3. **Given** an agent YAML file missing a required field (e.g., no `role`)\n   **When** validated against the agent schema\n   **Then** validation fails with errors identifying the missing required property by path\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n4. **Given** an agent YAML file with `personality.traits` where a trait value is outside 0-1 range (e.g., `rigor: 1.5`)\n   **When** validated against the agent schema\n   **Then** validation fails with an error identifying the out-of-range trait and its path\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n5. **Given** an agent YAML file with `personality.traits` where all values are within 0-1 range\n   **When** validated against the agent schema\n   **Then** validation passes (personality is optional; when present, traits are validated)\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n6. **Given** a `validateAgentSchema()` function exported from `src/lib/schema-validate.ts`\n   **When** called with valid agent config data\n   **Then** it returns `ValidationResult` with `{ valid: true, errors: [] }` using the same `validateAgainstSchema()` pattern as `validateWorkflowSchema()`\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n7. **Given** the `codeharness validate` command (story 2-5)\n   **When** agent YAML files exist in `.codeharness/agents/` or `templates/agents/`\n   **Then** the validate command can validate agent files against `agent.schema.json` (integration point — actual command wiring is story 3-2 or later; this story only ensures the schema + validation function are available)\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n8. **Given** unit tests for agent schema validation\n   **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n   **Then** tests pass covering: valid agent passes, missing required fields fail, traits outside 0-1 rejected, optional `personality` section accepted when present and valid, optional `disallowedTools` array accepted, unknown top-level properties rejected, and no regressions in existing schema-validate tests\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n## Tasks / Subtasks\n\n- [x] Task 1: Create the agent JSON schema (AC: #1, #4, #5)\n  - [x] Create `src/schemas/agent.schema.json` following the same JSON Schema draft-07 pattern as `workflow.schema.json`\n  - [x] Define required properties: `name`, `role` (with `title`, `purpose`), `persona` (with `identity`, `communication_style`, `principles`)\n  - [x] Define optional `personality` section with `traits` object where each value is a number constrained to 0-1 via `minimum: 0, maximum: 1`\n  - [x] Define optional `disallowedTools` as an array of strings (needed for evaluator agent)\n  - [x] Set `additionalProperties: false` at top level to reject unknown fields\n\n- [x] Task 2: Add agent schema validation function (AC: #6, #7)\n  - [x] Import agent schema in `src/lib/schema-validate.ts`\n  - [x] Compile the agent schema with Ajv (same pattern as workflow schema)\n  - [x] Export `validateAgentSchema(data: unknown): ValidationResult` that delegates to `validateAgainstSchema()`\n  - [x] Ensure the existing `validateWorkflowSchema()` and `validateAgainstSchema()` remain unchanged\n\n- [x] Task 3: Write unit tests (AC: #2, #3, #4, #5, #8)\n  - [x] Create `src/lib/__tests__/schema-validate-agent.test.ts` (or extend existing `schema-validate.test.ts`)\n  - [x] Test: valid agent config with all required fields passes\n  - [x] Test: valid agent config with optional `personality.traits` in 0-1 range passes\n  - [x] Test: missing `name` field fails\n  - [x] Test: missing `role` field fails\n  - [x] Test: missing `persona` field fails\n  - [x] Test: `personality.traits.rigor: 1.5` fails (above 1)\n  - [x] Test: `personality.traits.warmth: -0.1` fails (below 0)\n  - [x] Test: valid `disallowedTools: [\"Edit\", \"Write\"]` passes\n  - [x] Test: unknown top-level property rejected\n  - [x] Test: existing workflow schema validation still works (no regressions)\n\n## Dev Notes\n\n### Module Location and Architecture Role\n\nPer architecture-v2 AD1, `agent-resolver` resolves agent config through patch chain and compiles to SDK inline subagent definition (FR7-12). This story creates the **schema** that `agent-resolver` (story 3-3) will use for validation. The schema lives at `src/schemas/agent.schema.json` alongside the existing `workflow.schema.json`.\n\nThe validation function lives in `src/lib/schema-validate.ts` — the module already has a generic `validateAgainstSchema()` helper and a workflow-specific `validateWorkflowSchema()`. Add `validateAgentSchema()` following the exact same pattern.\n\n### Agent Config Shape (from PRD and Architecture)\n\nThe canonical agent config format from prd-evaluator-redesign.md:\n\n```yaml\nname: evaluator\nrole:\n  title: Adversarial QA Evaluator\n  purpose: Exercise the built artifact and determine if it actually works\npersona:\n  identity: Senior QA who trusts nothing without evidence\n  communication_style: Blunt, evidence-first\n  principles:\n    - Never give the benefit of the doubt\n    - Every PASS requires evidence\n# Optional: quantified personality\npersonality:\n  traits:\n    rigor: 0.98\n    directness: 0.95\n    warmth: 0.2\n```\n\n**Required fields:**\n- `name` (string) — agent identifier\n- `role.title` (string) — agent's role title\n- `role.purpose` (string) — what this agent does\n- `persona.identity` (string) — who this agent is\n- `persona.communication_style` (string) — how it communicates\n- `persona.principles` (array of strings) — behavioral principles\n\n**Optional fields:**\n- `personality.traits` — object with string keys and number values constrained to 0-1 range (PersonaNexus-compatible, FR10)\n- `disallowedTools` — array of strings (used by evaluator agent for source isolation, per AD2)\n\n### JSON Schema Pattern to Follow\n\nFollow the existing `workflow.schema.json` pattern exactly:\n- `\"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"`\n- `\"$id\": \"https://codeharness.dev/schemas/agent.schema.json\"`\n- Use `definitions` for reusable sub-schemas if needed\n- `additionalProperties: false` at all object levels\n\n### Trait Validation Detail\n\nPersonaNexus traits are an `additionalProperties` object where each value must be `{ \"type\": \"number\", \"minimum\": 0, \"maximum\": 1 }`. The trait names are not fixed — any string key is allowed as long as the value is 0-1. Use `additionalProperties` with a number schema inside the `traits` object.\n\n### What This Story Does NOT Do\n\n- Does NOT create agent YAML files (that's story 3-2)\n- Does NOT implement the agent resolver module (that's story 3-3)\n- Does NOT wire agent validation into the `validate` command (future integration — this story only provides the schema + validation function)\n- Does NOT implement patch resolution (extends, overrides, prompt_patches) — that's the resolver in story 3-3\n- Does NOT add `templates/agents/` to `package.json` `files` array (that's story 3-2)\n\n### Anti-Patterns to Avoid\n\n- **Do NOT create a separate Ajv instance** — reuse the existing one in `schema-validate.ts`\n- **Do NOT put schema validation logic in a new file** — extend `schema-validate.ts`\n- **Do NOT define trait names as an enum** — PersonaNexus traits are open-ended (any 0-1 number)\n- **Do NOT make `personality` required** — it's optional per FR10 (\"optional PersonaNexus-compatible traits\")\n- **Do NOT modify `workflow.schema.json`** — this story only adds agent schema\n\n### Dependencies from Previous Stories\n\n- **Story 2.1** established the `src/schemas/` directory and `workflow.schema.json` — same directory for `agent.schema.json`\n- **Story 2.1** established the `schema-validate.ts` module with `validateAgainstSchema()` — the generic helper to reuse\n- **Story 2.5** established the `validate` command with subcommand structure — future stories will wire agent validation into it\n\n### Existing Test Patterns\n\nFollow the pattern in existing tests:\n- Tests are co-located in `src/lib/__tests__/`\n- Use vitest (`describe`, `it`, `expect`)\n- Test both valid and invalid inputs\n- Assert on specific error paths and messages from `ValidationResult`\n\n### Git Intelligence\n\nRecent commits follow `feat: story X-Y-slug — description`. The codebase uses TypeScript with ESM (`\"type\": \"module\"`), vitest for testing, and tsup for building. All modules are single files in `src/lib/` with co-located tests in `__tests__/`.\n\n### Project Structure Notes\n\n- New file: `src/schemas/agent.schema.json` — the agent configuration JSON schema\n- Modified file: `src/lib/schema-validate.ts` — add `validateAgentSchema()` export\n- New test file: `src/lib/__tests__/schema-validate-agent.test.ts` (or extend existing test file)\n- No changes to any other existing files\n\n### References\n\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-v2.md#Story 3.1: Agent Config JSON Schema]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD1: Module Boundaries — agent-resolver module]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD3: Embedded Template Storage — templates/agents/]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#Agent Configuration Format — canonical YAML shape]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#FR7-FR12 — Agent Configuration FRs]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#NFR2 — Agent config resolution <200ms]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#NFR12 — BMAD agent configs read-only]\n- [Source: src/schemas/workflow.schema.json — pattern to follow for JSON schema structure]\n- [Source: src/lib/schema-validate.ts — existing validation module to extend]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/2-5-validate-command.md — validate command structure for future integration]\n\n<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n## Verification Requirements\n\n- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/3-1-agent-config-json-schema-proof.md)\n- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n\n## Documentation Requirements\n\n- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/3-1-agent-config-json-schema.md\n\n## Testing Requirements\n\n- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n\n## Dev Agent Record\n\n### Agent Model Used\n\nClaude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n\n### Debug Log References\n\n### Completion Notes List\n\n- All 3 tasks completed: schema, validation function, tests\n- 29 new agent schema tests pass, 28 existing workflow schema tests unaffected\n- Full test suite: 3662 tests pass across 148 files\n\n### Code Review Notes (Adversarial)\n\n- **Fixed**: Schema accepted empty strings for all fields — added `minLength: 1` to `name`, `role.title`, `role.purpose`, `persona.identity`, `persona.communication_style`, and principles items\n- **Fixed**: Schema accepted empty `principles` array — added `minItems: 1`\n- **Fixed**: Schema accepted `personality: {}` without `traits` key — made `traits` required inside `personality`\n- **Fixed**: Missing tests for empty string rejection, empty collection rejection, `personality` without `traits`, and non-string `disallowedTools` items\n- Post-review: 39 agent schema tests pass (was 29), 28 workflow schema tests unaffected\n- Coverage: 96.65% overall, all 152 files above 80% floor, `schema-validate.ts` at 100%\n\n### File List\n\n- `src/schemas/agent.schema.json` — new agent configuration JSON schema\n- `src/lib/schema-validate.ts` — added `validateAgentSchema()` export\n- `src/lib/__tests__/schema-validate-agent.test.ts` — new test file with 29 tests\n","numLines":238,"startLine":1,"totalLines":238}}}
